	.story This is a massive place that was recreated to depict the olden days of Jeju. In this folk village, you get to see the old houses made of mud, wood and leaves. Models of villagers show a snapshot of their daily life. The domesticated animals like ducks, cows, and pigs are real, however. Freshwater is hard to come by on a small island so the inhabitants resort to collecting rainwater in vats. By tying up dried grass and creating a platform to direct water into the vat, it creates a larger surface area to collect the rain.
