	h2 Korean Cuisine
	.story In this last part, I gathered all the photos of the Korean dishes we ate on the trip. You feel like you are hit by rainbow colors - red, white, green, yellow, brown, black, and white.	They come in many small dishes spread across the table. I especially like the kimchi, seaweed, and fat bean sprouts. Good chopstick skill is a must for an enjoyable eating experience. Another favorite style of eating is the hotpot soup filled to the brim with vegetables, mushroom, and meat. Breakfast tends to be congee and hot buns.
